    <string name="ca_limits_title">What on-device filtering can and cannot do</string>
    <string name="ca_limits_body">Installing this certificate lets WebFilter inspect the full content of traffic from apps that trust user certificates.\n\nURL, hostname (SNI), DNS-over-HTTPS and QUIC filtering work for every app routed through the VPN, even without the certificate.\n\nChrome and many hardened apps enforce Certificate Transparency and reject user-installed certificates. Their encrypted traffic is passed through untouched (blind-spliced) rather than broken, so deep content features (text/image NSFW classifiers, YouTube rewriting) do not apply to them.</string>

    <string name="per_app_hint">Selected apps are routed through the filter. Leave all unchecked to filter every app.</string>

